        <p>Trading bonus codes are promotional codes negotiated between affiliate partners (like TradeTheDay) and regulated brokers. These aren't random discounts - they're structured partnerships where brokers offer enhanced terms to incentivize new account openings through trusted referral channels.</p>

        <h5>Types of Trading Bonuses</h5>
        <p><strong>Welcome Deposit Bonuses:</strong> The most common type. You deposit money, the broker matches a percentage. Example: 20% bonus on $5,000 deposit = $1,000 extra trading capital. These typically have trading volume requirements before withdrawal.</p>

        <p><strong>No-Deposit Bonuses:</strong> Rare but valuable - free trading capital just for signing up. Usually smaller amounts ($20-$100) with strict withdrawal conditions. Great for testing a broker risk-free.</p>

        <p><strong>Cashback/Rebate Programs:</strong> Ongoing rewards rather than one-time bonuses. Earn money back on every trade - typically $2-$7 per lot traded. Over time, active traders can earn substantial amounts.</p>

        <p><strong>Demo Account Credits:</strong> Virtual money for practice trading. No real value but invaluable for learning without risk. eToro's $100,000 virtual portfolio is a prime example.</p>

        <h5>Why Brokers Offer Bonuses</h5>
        <p>Customer acquisition in the brokerage industry is expensive. Bonuses are essentially marketing costs - brokers know that once you're trading on their platform, you're likely to stay. The bonus costs them less than traditional advertising while providing measurable ROI. It's a win-win: you get extra capital, they get a new customer.</p>

        <h5>The Partner Code Advantage</h5>
        <p>Why use a partner code instead of signing up directly? Partner codes often unlock exclusive tiers unavailable to direct signups. Brokers reserve their best offers for affiliate partnerships because these channels deliver higher-quality, more engaged customers. Our AvaTrade partner code 128979, for example, provides bonus tiers up to $10,000 - higher than the standard direct signup offers.</p>
